==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: FM
<hw>FM</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>F</ets>requency
<ets>M</ets>odulaiton.]</ety> <def>A method of transmitting radio
signals by modulating the frequency of the carrier wave; -- opposed to
AM (amplitude modulation), in which the signal modulates the amplitude,
rather than the frequency of the carrier wave.</def>
<mark>[acron.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> frequency modulation.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fm</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Fm
<hw>Fm</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>The chemical symbol for
<er>Fermium</er>, a transuranic element.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fermium, atomic number 100.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

